  "body": "Part of #7903 \r\n\r\nOpening this issue to track error revamp across Prysm beacon node and validator. We have errors with incorrect verbosity and wrap usages. The verbosity level will be defined as the following:\r\n```\r\nlog.Trace(\"Something very low level.\")\r\nlog.Debug(\"Useful debugging information.\")\r\nlog.Info(\"Something noteworthy happened!\")\r\nlog.Warn(\"You should probably take a look at this.\")\r\nlog.Error(\"Something failed but I'm not quitting.\")\r\n// Calls os.Exit(1) after logging\r\nlog.Fatal(\"Bye.\")\r\n// Calls panic() after logging\r\nlog.Panic(\"I'm bailing.\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nWe'll go through each package and reflect it's changes in the tracking below ðŸ‘‡ \r\n* Beacon chain\r\n    * blockchain\r\n    * cache\r\n    * core\r\n    * db\r\n    * forkchoice\r\n    * operations\r\n    * p2p\r\n    * powchain\r\n    * sync\r\n    * rpc\r\n    * state\r\n* Validator\r\n    * accounts\r\n    * client\r\n    * db\r\n    * keymanager\r\n    * rpc\r\n    * slashing protection\r\n    * web\r\n\r\nReadings:\r\nhttps://dave.cheney.net/2016/06/12/stack-traces-and-the-errors-package\r\nhttps://www.honeybadger.io/blog/golang-logging/",
